Taxonomic heatmap

Each column of the heatmap represents one sample and each row represents one taxon, typically a genus. Taxa were included in the chart if the abundance in any sample exceeded 1%.

The chart is colored white if taxa were not observed in the sample, dark blue if taxa were observed at very low abundance. This allows the reader to quickly survey presence/absence. Abundance values exceeding 40% are colored red, indicating an extremely dominant species.

Alpha diversity

Alpha diversity was assessed by the expected number of observed OTUs (out of rarefying sample size of 20), Shannon index, and Faith’s phylogenetic diversity.

Beta diversity

Similarity between samples was assessed by weighted and unweighted UniFrac distances.
